`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The signal-based tutorial pattern mirrors how quest objectives work: game actions emit string signals (`"action:plant"`, `"action:dig"`), and the state machine checks the signal against the current step's expected trigger. This keeps the tutorial system fully decoupled from the input system and ECS — no imports of Three.js, Rapier, or React needed. Tests can call `tickTutorial(state, signal)` directly with no mocks.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
